text:

Any practical tips are welcome.

Show HN: AI Runner v1.8.4 Stable Diffusion: controlnet, drawing tools and more
text:
AI Runner is a project I have been working on for several months. It allows users to use Stable Diffusion locally on their own hardware without the need to install any additional dependencies (such as python, drivers etc).

It is currently limited to nvidia hardware and generates 512x512 images in approximately 2 seconds on an RTX 2080s.

Here's what has changed since last time I posted about it:

- Switched from tkinter to PyQT for better performance

- Removed image gallery and model database as these were bloat

- Added support for textual inversion (embeddings)

- Added support for controlnet

- Added drawing and erasing tools

- Added layers

- Added a dark mode theme

- Improved model downloading experience

- Added better support for file saving / exporting / importing

- Fixed lots of bugs

If you're looking for an easy way to run Stable Diffusion that doesn't require any technical knowledge and offers an infinite canvas for easy outpainting, be sure to check it out.
